# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Link-check ignore list.
#
# One regex per line (Python `re` syntax).  Matching URLs are excluded from
# pass/fail accounting by `scripts/audit_links.py`.
#
# Add an entry ONLY for a domain that (a) is *known* to be reachable by a
# browser and (b) reliably blocks automated HEAD/GET from CI runners — e.g.
# anti-bot WAFs, rate-limit throttles, or Cloudflare challenges.  For content
# that has genuinely moved or been deleted, fix the URL instead of silencing
# the check.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Cloudflare / anti-bot WAFs --------------------------------------------

# Man-page mirrors protected by Cloudflare captcha.
^https?://linux\.die\.net/

# cyberciti.biz serves 403 to non-browser agents but works in browsers.
^https?://www\.cyberciti\.biz/

# admx.help times out from scripted requests.
^https?://admx\.help/

# Sophos news redirects infinitely for HEAD.
^https?://news\.sophos\.com/

# Cisco support portal regularly 403s anonymous crawlers.
^https?://www\.cisco\.com/c/

# Trustwave SpiderLabs blog — consistent 403 for scripted agents.
^https?://www\.trustwave\.com/

# Portswigger research blog — rate-limits automated crawlers.
^https?://portswigger\.net/

# --- Microsoft Learn aggressive 429 throttling ------------------------------
# learn.microsoft.com returns 429 to concurrent HEAD/GET from CI runners but
# serves the content fine in a browser.  Rate-limiting is per-IP.
^https?://learn\.microsoft\.com/

# --- GitHub / community platforms -------------------------------------------
# github.com and raw.githubusercontent.com both rate-limit unauthenticated
# HEAD requests.  For private-repo links or permalinks, use a token-based
# checker locally.
^https?://github\.com/
^https?://raw\.githubusercontent\.com/

# Medium and its user subdomains return 403 to unauthenticated bots.
^https?://([a-z0-9-]+\.)?medium\.com/

